3 SECTION 2.2. G.S. 105-507.2 reads as rewritten:
4 "§ 105-507.2. Levy and collection Levy, collection, and repeal of sales and use tax.
5 (a) If the majority of those voting in a referendum held pursuant to G.S. 105-507.1 vote
6 for the levy of the tax, the board of commissioners of the county may, by resolution, levy one-half
7 percent (½%) local sales and use taxes in addition to any other State and local sales and use taxes
8 levied pursuant to law. Except as provided in this Part, the adoption, levy, collection,
9 administration, and repeal of these additional taxes shall be in accordance with Article 39 of this
10 Chapter. In applying the provisions of Article 39 of this Chapter to this Part, references to "this
11 Article" mean "Part 1 of Article 43 of Chapter 105 of the General Statutes".
12 (b) No action by a county to repeal a tax levied under this Part may become effective
13 while previously issued or, as provided in this subsection, refinanced, bonds, notes, or other
14 financing secured or payable by receipts derived from the tax allocated to a municipality or a
15 transportation authority by the county remain outstanding. Nothing in this Part obligates a county
16 to exercise any power of taxation or restricts the ability of the county to repeal the tax previously
17 levied. If a county repeals a tax levied under this Part, a municipality or transportation authority
18 may refinance previously issued bonds, notes, or other financing that are secured or payable by
19 receipts for the tax revenue under this Part to reduce debt service as allowed under the law so
20 long as the refinancing does not extend the date of maturity for the previously issued bonds,
21 notes, or other financing."
