1 quarantines, acts of the federal or State government, a declared state of
2 emergency, strikes or labor disruptions other than those specific to the
3 Authority, or other conditions beyond its reasonable control and which, by
4 reasonable diligence, the Authority is unable to prevent. Should a force
5 majeure event delay or halt the Red Line project, the Authority shall resume
6 the original Red Line schedule as soon as practicable when the force majeure
7 event has ceased or subsided. Planning, design, and construction work may
8 occur simultaneously on other rail projects, but only to the extent that those
9 activities do not interfere with or delay the completion of the Red Line.
10 (3) The Authority shall solicit input from the Towns of Cornelius, Davidson, and
11 Huntersville on all aspects of the Red Line design, including conceptual
12 design, construction drawings, and station location. If the Red Line extends to
13 the Town of Mooresville, the Authority shall also solicit input from that Town.
14 (4) The Authority shall reimburse the City of Charlotte for the acquisition of the
15 Norfolk Southern O-Line and related property. The amount to be reimbursed
16 may not be more than the cost to the City of Charlotte to acquire the property
17 from Norfolk Southern, including any costs for indebtedness incurred by the
18 City with respect to the acquisition. The Authority and the City of Charlotte
19 shall jointly agree to a schedule for reimbursement of these costs.
20 SECTION 4.10. Repeal of Tax. – The Mecklenburg County Board of
21 Commissioners may by resolution repeal the levy and imposition of the tax in the County as
22 provided in G.S. 105-473(c). The Board of Commissioners, upon adoption of a repeal resolution,
23 shall cause a certified copy of the resolution to be delivered immediately to the Secretary of
24 Revenue. No liability for any tax levied under this Part that attached prior to the effective date
25 on which a levy is repealed shall be discharged as a result of such repeal, and no right to a refund
26 of tax or otherwise that accrued prior to the effective date on which a levy is repealed shall be
27 denied as a result of such repeal. If a county repeals a tax levied under this Part, the Authority or
28 a municipality may refinance previously issued bonds, notes, or other financing that are secured
29 or payable by receipts for the tax revenue under this Part to reduce debt service as allowed under
30 the law so long as the refinancing does not extend the date of maturity for the previously issued
31 bonds, notes, or other financing. No repeal of taxes levied and imposed under this Part shall be
32 effective until the latest of the following:
33 (1) The end of the fiscal year in which the repeal resolution was adopted.
34 (2) The date by which all previously issued or, as provided in this section,
35 refinanced, bonds, notes, or other financing obtained by the Authority or a
36 municipality secured or payable by receipts from the tax levied under this Part
37 have been satisfied.
38 (3) The date by which the Authority has fully reimbursed the City for the purchase
39 of the O-Line as required by Section 4.9(4) of this act.
40 SECTION 4.11. Study. – If a referendum held pursuant to this Part fails, then within
41 one year after the failed referendum the Charlotte Area Transit System shall develop and publish
42 a comprehensive, long-term public transportation plan that specifically includes frequent, express
43 public transportation connections between the center of the City of Charlotte and Charlotte
44 Douglas International Airport.
