General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 (3) Financial, legal, or operational commitments with respect to the county that is
2 to be added to the territorial jurisdiction of the authority.
3 (4) Any other matter determined to be relevant by the board of trustees and the
4 board of commissioners of the affected county.
5 "§ 160A-907. Voting; removal.
6 (a) A majority of the board of trustees constitutes a quorum for the transaction of
7 business. Each member shall have one vote.
8 (b) Each member of the board of trustees may be removed with or without cause by the
9 appointing authority.
10 (c) Appointments to fill vacancies shall be made for the remainder of the unexpired term
11 by the respective appointing authority charged with the responsibility for making such
12 appointments pursuant to G.S. 160A-905. All members shall serve until their successors are
13 appointed and qualified, unless removed from office.
14 "§ 160A-908. Advisory committees.
15 The board of trustees may provide for the selection of such advisory committees as it may
16 find appropriate, which may or may not include members of the board of trustees.
17 "§ 160A-909. Purpose of the authority.
18 The purpose of the authority shall be to finance, provide, operate, and maintain for a safe,
19 clean, reliable, adequate, convenient, energy efficient, economically, and environmentally sound
20 public transportation system for the service area of the authority through the granting of
21 franchises, ownership, and leasing of terminals, buses, and other transportation facilities and
22 equipment, and otherwise through the exercise of the powers and duties conferred upon it, in
23 order to enhance mobility in the region and encourage sound growth patterns. Such a service,
24 facility, or function shall be financed, provided, operated, or maintained in the service area of the
25 authority either in addition to or to a greater or lesser extent than services, facilities, or functions
26 are financed, provided, operated, or maintained for the entirety of the respective units of local
27 government. An authority may take direct action to accomplish these purposes or may enter
28 agreements with another unit of local government in the service area of the authority or a private
29 entity to accomplish these purposes.
30 "§ 160A-910. Service area of the authority.
31 The service area of the authority shall be as determined by the board of trustees consistent
32 with its purpose but shall not exceed the sum of the following:
33 (1) The territorial jurisdiction of the authority.
34 (2) An area outside of the territorial jurisdiction of the authority provided that one
35 of the following conditions is satisfied:
36 a. If the area is within this State, the governing bodies of the political
37 subdivisions to which service is to be extended approved by majority
38 vote of their governing boards the extension of service into the
39 political subdivision or the purchase of real property within the
40 political subdivision for the extension of service.
41 b. If the area is in another state, the extension of service is approved by
42 any applicable federal or State agency and in accordance with the other
43 state's laws.
44 "§ 160A-911. General powers of the authority.
45 The general powers of the authority include all of the following:
46 (1) To sue and be sued.
47 (2) To have a seal.
48 (3) To make rules and regulations, not inconsistent with this Article, for its
49 organization and internal management.
