13 "§ 160A-912. Authority of Utilities Commission not affected.
14 (a) Except as otherwise provided in this Article, nothing in this Article shall be construed
15 to limit or otherwise affect the power or authority of the North Carolina Utilities Commission or
16 the right of appeal to the North Carolina Utilities Commission as provided by law.
17 (b) The North Carolina Utilities Commission shall not have jurisdiction over rates, fees,
18 charges, routes, and schedules of an authority for service within its territorial jurisdiction.
19 "§ 160A-913. Fiscal accountability.
20 An authority is a public authority subject to the provisions of Chapter 159 of the General
21 Statutes.
22 "§ 160A-914. Funds.
23 The establishment and operation of an authority are governmental functions and constitute a
24 public purpose, and the State of North Carolina and any unit of local government may appropriate
25 funds to support the establishment and operation of the authority. The State of North Carolina
26 and any unit of local government may also dedicate, sell, convey, donate, or lease any of their
27 interests in any property to the authority. An authority may apply for grants from the State of
28 North Carolina, or from the United States or any department, agency, or instrumentality thereof.
29 The Department of Transportation may allocate to an authority any funds appropriated for public
30 transportation or any funds whose use is not restricted by law.
31 "§ 160A-915. Competition.
32 No equipment of the authority may be used for charter, tour, or sightseeing service except as
33 allowed under regulations adopted by the Federal Transit Administration.
34 "§ 160A-916. Effect on existing franchises and operations.
35 Creation of the authority shall not have an effect on any existing franchises granted by any
36 unit of local government; such existing franchises shall continue in full force and effect until
37 legally terminated; further, all ordinances and resolutions of the unit of local government
38 regulating local public transportation systems, bus operations, and taxicabs shall continue in full
39 force and effect now and in the future, unless superseded by regulations of the authority; such
40 superseding, if any, may occur only on the basis of prior mutual agreement between the authority
41 and the respective unit of local government.
42 "§ 160A-917. Termination.
43 The board of trustees may terminate the existence of the authority by adopting a resolution
44 by majority vote to do so at any time when it has no outstanding indebtedness. The resolution to
45 terminate the existence of the authority does not become effective unless and until ratified by
46 majority vote of the board of commissioners of the county that created the authority. In the event
47 of such termination, all property and assets of the authority not otherwise encumbered shall
48 become the property of a unit of local government within the territorial jurisdiction of the
49 authority as specified in the termination resolution and, if accepted by the unit of local
50 government, the unit of local government shall succeed to all rights, obligations, and liabilities
51 of the authority.
