1 "§ 160A-918. Controlling provisions.
2 Insofar as the provisions of this Article are not consistent with the provisions of any other
3 law, public or private, the provisions of this Article shall be controlling.
4 "§ 160A-919. Bonds and notes authorized.
5 In addition to the powers granted by this Article, the authority may issue bonds and notes
6 pursuant to the provisions of The State and Local Government Revenue Bond Act, Article 5 of
7 Chapter 159 of the General Statutes, for the purpose of financing public transportation systems
8 or any part thereof and to refund such bonds and notes and to refund any bonds, notes, or other
9 obligations of another municipality used to finance or refinance real and personal property for a
10 public transportation system to be owned or operated by the authority, whether or not in advance
11 of their maturity or earliest redemption date.
12 "§ 160A-920. Equipment trust certificates.
13 In addition to the powers here and before granted, the authority shall have continuing power
14 to purchase equipment, and in connection therewith execute agreements, leases with or without
15 option to purchase, or equipment trust certificates. All money required to be paid by the authority
16 under the provisions of such agreements, leases with or without option to purchase, and
17 equipment trust certificates shall be payable solely from the fares, fees, rentals, charges, revenues,
18 and earnings of the authority, monies derived from the sale of any surplus property of the
19 authority, and gifts, grants, and contributions from any source whatever. Payment for such
20 equipment or rentals may be made in installments; the deferred installments may be evidenced
21 by equipment trust certificates payable solely from the aforesaid revenues or receipts and title to
22 such equipment may or may not vest in the authority until the equipment trust certificates are
23 paid.
24 "§ 160A-921. Power of eminent domain.
25 (a) The authority shall have continuing power to acquire, by gift, grant, devise, exchange,
26 purchase, lease with or without option to purchase, or any other lawful method, including the
27 power of eminent domain, the fee or any lesser interest in real or personal property for use by the
28 authority.
29 (b) Exercise of the power of eminent domain by the authority shall be in accordance with
30 Chapters 40A and 136 of the General Statutes.
31 "§ 160A-922. Tax exemption.
32 The property of the authority, both real and personal, its acts, activities, and income shall be
33 exempt from any tax or tax obligation; in the event of any lease of authority property, or other
34 arrangement which amounts to a leasehold interest, to a private party, this exemption shall not
35 apply to the value of such leasehold interest nor shall it apply to the income of the lessee.
36 Otherwise, however, for the purpose of taxation, when property of the authority is leased to
37 private parties solely for the purpose of the authority, the acts and activities of the lessee shall be
38 considered as the acts and activities of the authority and the exemption. The interest on bonds or
39 obligations issued by the authority shall be exempt from State taxes.
40 "§ 160A-923. Removal and relocation of utility structures.
41 (a) The authority shall have the power to require any public utility, railroad, or other
42 public service corporation owning or operating any installations, structures, equipment,
43 apparatus, appliances, or facilities in, upon, under, over, across, or along any ways on which the
44 authority has the right to own, construct, operate, or maintain its public transportation system, to
45 relocate such installation, structures, equipment, apparatus, appliances, or facilities from their
46 locations, or, in the sole discretion of the affected public utility, railroad, or other public service
47 corporation, to remove such installations, structures, equipment, apparatus, appliances, or
48 facilities from their locations.
49 (b) If the owner or operator thereof fails or refuses to relocate them, the authority may
50 proceed to do so.
