37 PART VII. REVENUE BONDS
38 SECTION 7.1. The definitions in G.S. 159-81 apply in this Part.
39 SECTION 7.2. In addition to the revenues included in G.S. 159-81(4), a
40 municipality may include as revenues the receipts from any sales and use tax or other local tax
41 received by a municipality in connection with its ownership and operation of a revenue bond
42 project or a utility or public service enterprise facility or system of which a revenue bond project
43 is a part as long as the pledge of such receipts does not constitute a pledge of the municipality's
44 taxing power.
45 SECTION 7.3. In addition to the powers provided in G.S. 159-83, a municipality
46 has the authority to finance and refinance the cost of public transportation systems, facilities, or
47 equipment with bonds or notes secured in one or more of the following ways: (i) by the revenues
48 of the public transportation systems, facilities, or equipment, (ii) by pledge, mortgage, or grant
49 of a security interest in all or a portion of the real and personal property, whether owned or leased,
50 comprising the public transportation systems, facilities, or equipment, and (iii) as otherwise
51 provided in Article 5 of Chapter 159 of the General Statutes. Notwithstanding anything in
Page 22 House Bill 948-Fifth Edition

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 G.S. 159-83(a) or otherwise in Article 5 of Chapter 159 of the General Statutes to the contrary,
2 each municipality may secure bonds or notes by a pledge of all or any portion of the revenues of
3 public transportation systems, facilities, or equipment without regard to meeting the expense and
4 maintenance and operation of and renewals and replacements with respect to the revenue bond
5 project.
6 SECTION 7.4. This Part applies only to cities with a population of greater than
7 870,000 according to the 2020 federal decennial census or any subsequent federal decennial
8 census and metropolitan public transportation authorities created under Article 34 of Chapter
9 160A of the General Statutes, as enacted by Part V of this act.
